-Marchetti SM.1019|SM-1019]]) (disbanded on 20 September 1989)\n**** 440th Recon Helicopters Squadron ([[Bell 206|AB-206]]) (reassigned to the 54th Squadrons Group \"Cefeo\" on 20 September 1989)\n*** 34th Army Air Aviation Squadrons Group \"[[Taurus (constellation)|Toro]]\", at [[Venaria Reale|Venaria Reale Air Base]]\n**** 441st Recon Helicopters Squadron ([[Bell 206|AB-206]])\n**** 544th Multirole Helicopters Squadrons ([[Bell 204/205|AB-205]])\n*** 44th Recon Helicopters Squadrons Group \"[[Phoenix (constellation)|Fenice]]\", at [[Belluno Airport|Belluno Air Base]]\n**** 441st Recon Helicopters Squadron ([[Bell 206|AB-206]])\n**** 544th Multirole Helicopters Squadron ([[Bell 204/205|AB-205]])\n*** 54th Multirole Helicopters Squadrons Group \"[[Cepheus (constellation)|Cefeo]]\", at Bolzano-San Giacomo Air Base\n**** 541st Multirole Helicopters Squadrons ([[Bell 204/205|AB-205]])\n**** 542nd Multirole Helicopters Squadrons ([[Bell 204/205|AB-205]])\n**** 543rd Multirole Helicopters Squadrons ([[Bell 204/205|AB-205]])\n** [[File:CoA mil ITA rgt cavalleria 03.png|25px]] [[Regiment \"Savoia Cavalleria\" (3rd)|3rd Armored Squadrons Group \"Savoia Cavalleria\"]], in Merano, (two Leopard 1A2 tank companies and one VCC-2 mech infantry company)\n** [[File:CoA mil ITA rgt logistico 24.png|25px]] 24th Maneuver Logistic Battalion \"[[Dolomites|Dolomiti]]\", in Bolzano\n** 7th Armored [[Carabinieri]] Battalion \"[[Gold Medal of Military Valor|M.O.]] Petrucelli\", in [[Laives]], (one [[M47 Patton]] tank company, two M113 mech infantry companies and one M113/120mm heavy mortars company)\n** Alpini Paratroopers Company \"[[Matterhorn|Monte Cervino]]\", in [[Eppan an der Weinstra\u00dfe|Appiano]]\n\n==== Alpine Brigade \"Taurinense\" ====\n* [[File:CoA mil ITA alp bde Taurinense.png|30px]] '''[[Alpine Brigade Taurinense|Alpine Brigade \"Taurinense\"]]''', in [[Turin]]\n** Command and Signal Unit \"Taurinense\", in Turin\n** [[File:CoA mil ITA rgt alpini 002.png|25px]] Alpini Battalion \"[[Saluzzo]]\", in [[Borgo San Dalmazzo]]\n** [[File:CoA mil ITA rgt alpini 003.png|25px]] Alpini Battalion \"[[Susa, Piedmont|Susa]]\", in [[Pinerolo]]\n** [[File:CoA mil ITA btg alpini Mondov\u00ec.png|25px]] Alpini (Recruits Training) Battalion \"[[Mondov\u00ec]]\", in [[Cuneo]]\n** [[File:CoA 1 Artimon Rgt.svg|25px]] (*)Mountain Artillery Group \"[[Aosta]]\", in [[Saluzzo]], ([[M114 155 mm howitzer|M114 155mm]] towed [[howitzer]]s)\n** [[File:CoA 4 Artimon Rgt.png|25px]] Mountain Artillery Group \"Pinerolo, in Susa, ([[OTO Melara Mod 56|M56 105mm]] pack [[howitzer]]s)\n** [[File:CoA mil ITA btg log taurinense.png|25px]] (*)Logistic Battalion \"Taurinense\", in [[Rivoli, Piedmont|Rivoli]]\n** (*)Anti-tank Company \"Taurinense\", in Turin\n** Engineer Company \"Taurinense\", in [[Abbadia Alpina]]\n** (*)Airmobile Medical Unit \"Taurinense\", in [[Rivoli, Piedmont|Rivoli]]\n* The units marked with an (*) were earmarked for the NATO [[Allied_Command_Europe_Mobile_Force#ACE_Mobile_Force_(Land)|AMF(L) (Allied Mobile Force (Land))]]\n\n==== Alpine Brigade \"Orobica\" ====\n* [[File:CoA mil ITA alp bde Orobica.png|30px]] '''[[Alpine Brigade Orobica|Alpine Brigade \"Orobica\"]]''', in [[Meran|Merano]]\n** Command and Signal Unit \"[[Bergamasque Alps|Orobica]]\", in Merano\n** [[File:CoA mil ITA rgt alpini 005.png|25px]] Alpini Battalion \"[[Morbegno]]\", in [[Sterzing|Vipiteno]]\n** [[File:CoA mil ITA btg alpini tirano.png|25px]] Alpini Battalion \"[[Tirano]]\", in [[Mals|Malles Venosta]]\n** [[File:CoA mil ITA rgt alpini 018.png|25px]] Alpini (Recruits Training) Battalion \"[[Edolo]]\", in [[Meran]]\n** [[File:CoA 5 Artimon Rgt.png|25px]] Mountain Artillery Group \"[[Bergamo]]\", in [[Schlanders|Silandro]], ([[OTO Melara Mod 56|M56 105mm]] pack [[howitzer]]s) \n** [[File:CoA mil ITA gr artiglieria sondrio.png|25px]] Mountain Artillery Group \"[[Sondrio]]\", in Silandro, ([[M114 155 mm howitzer|M114 155mm]] towed [[howitzer]]s, disbanded 1989, howitzers reassigned