/Comando-Forze-Operative-Sud/Divisione-Acqui/Brigata-Meccanizzata-Aosta/Pagine/RCST-Aosta.aspx |publisher=Esercito Italiano |accessdate=16 November 2018}}</ref>\n** [[File:CoA mil ITA rgt fanteria 005.png|25px]] 5th Motorized Infantry Battalion \"Col della Berretta\", in Messina<ref name='\"Aosta\"'/><ref>{{cite web |title=5\u00b0 Reggimento Fanteria \"Aosta\" - La Storia |url=http://www.esercito.difesa.it/organizzazione/capo-di-sme/Comando-Forze-Operative-Sud/Divisione-Acqui/Brigata-Meccanizzata-Aosta/5-Reggimento-Fanteria-Aosta/Pagine/La-Storia.aspx |publisher=Esercito Italiano |accessdate=16 November 2018}}</ref>\n** [[File:CoA mil ITA rgt fanteria 062.png|25px]] 62nd Motorized Infantry Battalion \"Sicilia\", in Catania<ref name='\"Aosta\"'/><ref>{{cite web |title=62\u00b0 Reggimento Fanteria \"Sicilia\" - La Storia |url=http://www.esercito.difesa.it/organizzazione/capo-di-sme/Comando-Forze-Operative-Sud/Divisione-Acqui/Brigata-Meccanizzata-Aosta/62-Reggimento-Fanteria-Sicilia/Pagine/La-Storia.aspx |publisher=Esercito Italiano |accessdate=16 November 2018}}</ref>\n** [[File:CoA mil ITA rgt fanteria 141.png|25px]] 141st Motorized Infantry Battalion \"Catanzaro\", in [[Palermo]]<ref name='\"Aosta\"'/><ref>{{cite book |last1=Franco dell'Uomo, Rodolfo Puletti |title=L'Esercito Italiano verso il 2000 - Volume Primo - Tomo I |date=1998 |publisher=Stato Maggiore dell'Esercito - Ufficio Storico |location=Rome |page=373}}</ref>\n** [[File:CoA mil ITA btg carri 062.png|25px]] 62nd Armored Battalion \"[[Gold Medal of Military Valor|M.O.]] Jero\", in [[Catania]] (two Leopard 1A2 tanks companies and one M113 mech infantry company)<ref name='\"Aosta\"'/><ref>{{cite book |last1=Franco dell'Uomo, Roberto di Rosa |title=L'Esercito Italiano verso il 2000 - Volume Secondo - Tomo I |date=2001 |publisher=Stato Maggiore dell'Esercito - Ufficio Storico |location=Rome |page=533}}</ref>\n** [[File:CoA mil ITA rgt artiglieria 024.png|25px]] 24th Field Artillery Group \"Peloritani\", in Messina, with [[M114 155 mm howitzer|M114 155mm towed howitzers]]<ref name='\"Aosta\"'/><ref>{{cite web |title=24\u00b0 Reggimento artiglieria terrestre \"Peloritani\" - La Storia |url=http://www.esercito.difesa.it/organizzazione/capo-di-sme/Comando-Forze-Operative-Sud/Divisione-Acqui/Brigata-Meccanizzata-Aosta/24-Reggimento-artiglieria-terrestre-Peloritani/pagine/la-storia.aspx |publisher=Esercito Italiano |accessdate=16 November 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |last1=Franco dell'Uomo, Rodolfo Puletti |title=L'Esercito Italiano verso il 2000 - Volume Primo - Tomo II |date=1998 |publisher=Stato Maggiore dell'Esercito - Ufficio Storico |location=Rome |page=119}}</ref>\n** [[File:CoA mil ITA btg logistico aosta.png|25px]] Logistic Battalion \"Aosta\", in Messina<ref name='\"Aosta\"'/>\n** Anti-tank Company \"Aosta\", in Messina\n** Engineer Company \"Aosta\", in [[Syracuse, Sicily|Syracuse]]\n\n=== Sardinia Military Command ===\n* '''Sardinia Military Command''' (CMS), in [[Cagliari]], responsible for the island of [[Sardinia]]\n** CMS Command Unit, in Cagliari\n** [[File:CoA mil ITA rgt fanteria 045.png|25px]] 45th Infantry (Recruits Training) Battalion \"[[Arborea]]\", in [[Macomer]]\n** 21st Army Light Aviation Squadrons Group \"[[Ursa Major|Orsa Maggiore]]\", at [[Cagliari Elmas Airport|Cagliari-Elmas Air Base]]\n***211st Light Airplanes Squadron ([[SIAI-Marchetti SM.1019|SM-1019]])\n*** 421st Recon Helicopters Squadron ([[Bell 206|AB-206]])\n*** 521st Multirole Helicopters Squadron ([[Bell 205|AB-205]])\n** [[File:CoA mil ITA btg trasmissioni 047.png|25px]] 47th Signal Battalion \"[[Gennargentu]]\", in Cagliari\n** 12th Mixed Transport Unit, in Cagliari\n** 12th Supply Unit, in [[Nuoro]]\n** 12th Medical Company, in Cagliari\n** 12th Provisions Supply Company, in Cagliari\n** Military Hospital Type B, in Cagliari\n\n==== Motorized Brigade \"Sassari\" ====\n* [[File:CoA mil ITA mec bde Sassari.png|30px]] '''[[Sassari Mechanized Brigade|Motorized Brigade \"Sassari\"]]''', in [[Sassari]]\n** Command and Signal Unit \"Sassari\", in Sassari\n** [[File:CoA mil ITA rgt carri 001.png|25px]] [[1st Armored Regiment (Italy)|1st Armored Infantry (Training) Regiment]], in [[Teulada, Sardinia|Capo Teulada]]\n*** 1st Armored Infantry Battalion\n**** Command Company \n**** 1st Tank Company, 16x [[Leopard 1|Leopard 1A2]] [[main battle tank]]s\n**** 2nd Bersaglieri Company, 13x [[M113 armored personnel carrier|M113]] [[armored personnel carrier]]s\n**** Reconnaissance Helicopter Squadron, 6x [[Bell 206|AB-206]] helicopters\n**** Self-propelled Artillery Battery, 6x [[M109 howitzer|M109 155mm]] \n*** 2nd Armored Infantry Battalion (Reserve)\n*** Logistic Unit\n** [[File:CoA mil ITA rgt fanteria 151.png|25px]] 151st Motorized Infantry Battalion \"[[Sette Comuni]]\", in Cagliari\n** [[File:CoA mil ITA rgt fanteria 152.png|25px]] 152nd Motorized Infantry Battalion \"Sassari\", in Sassari\n** 170th Artillery Group (Reserve)\n\n=== Anti-aircraft Artillery Command ===\n* [[File:CoA mil ITA cdo artiglieria controaerei.png|30px]] '''Anti-aircraft Artillery Command''', in [[Padua]]\n** Command Unit, in Padua\n** [[File:CoA mil ITA rgt artiglieria c a 004.png|25px]] 4th Anti-aircraft Missile Artillery Regiment \"[[Peschiera del Garda|Peschiera]]\", in [[Mantua]]\n*** Command Battery, Mantua\n*** 1st Anti-aircraft Missile Artillery Group, in [[Ravenna]], ([[MIM-23 Hawk]] [[surface-to-air missile]]s)\n*** 2nd Anti-aircraft Missile Artillery Group, in Mantua, (MIM-23 Hawk surface-to-air missiles)\n*** 24th Signal Company, in Mantua\n** [[File:CoA mil ITA rgt artiglieria c a 005.png|25px]] 5th Anti-aircraft Missile Artillery Regiment \"[[Pescara]]\", in [[Mestre]]\n*** Command Battery, Mestre\n*** 1st Anti-aircraft Missile Artillery Group, in [[San Don\u00e0 di Piave]], (MIM-23 Hawk surface-to-air missiles)\n*** 2nd Anti-aircraft Missile Artillery Group, in [[Rovigo]], (MIM-23 Hawk surface-to-air missiles)\n*** 25th Signal Company, in Mestre\n** [[File:CoA mil 