{"title_page": "E3 2013", "text_new": "{{Infobox Convention\n| name = Electronic Entertainment Expo 2013\n| image = E3 Expo 2013.jpg\n| caption = E3 Expo 2013 at the Los Angeles Convention Center showing the South Hall Entrance\n| genre = Multi-genre\n| begins = June 11, 2013\n| ends = June 13, 2013\n| venue = [[Los Angeles Convention Center]]\n| location = [[Los Angeles]], [[California]]\n| country = [[United States]]\n| prev = [[E3 2012]]\n| next = [[E3 2014]]\n| organizer = [[Entertainment Software Association]]\n| attendance = 48,200\n| filing = Non-profit\n}}\n\nThe '''Electronic Entertainment Expo 2013''' ('''E3 2013''') was the 19th [[Electronic Entertainment Expo]] held. The event took place at the [[Los Angeles Convention Center]] in [[Los Angeles]], [[California]]. It began on June 11, 2013, and ended on June 13, 2013, with 48,200 total attendees.<ref name=autogenerated1>{{cite web |title=E3 2013 Exhibitor Directory |url=http://e313.mapyourshow.com/5_0/search.cfm? |publisher=Entertainment Software Association |accessdate=18 June 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130613100422/http://e313.mapyourshow.com/5_0/search.cfm |archivedate=13 June 2013 }}</ref>\n\nThe main highlights included details of two major next-generation consoles, Microsoft's [[Xbox One]] and Sony's [[PlayStation 4]], as well as Nintendo's unveilings of ''[[Super Mario 3D World]]'', ''[[Mario Kart 8]]'', and ''[[Super Smash Bros. for Nintendo 3DS and Wii U]]''.<ref>{{cite news|title=E3 2013: is the games industry making real progress?|url=https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2013/jun/17/e3-2013-games-ps4-xbox-one|accessdate=18 June 2013|newspaper=The Guardian|date=2013-06-17|author=Simon Parkin}}</ref><ref name = wp>{{cite web|title=E3 2013: New titles make a big splash after years of sequels|url=https://articles.washingtonpost.com/2013-06-13/business/39937796_1_wii-u-big-studio-titles-the-electronic-entertainment-expo|publisher=The Washington Post|accessdate=18 June 2013|author=Hayley Tsukayama|date=2013-06-13}}</ref>\n\n==Press conferences==\n{{hatnote|All times in [[Pacific Daylight Time]] (UTC-7)}}\n\n[[Konami]], [[Microsoft Studios|Microsoft]], [[Electronic Arts]], [[Ubisoft]], and [[Sony Computer Entertainment|Sony]] all hosted press conferences during the conference.<ref>{{cite web|author=Kirk Hamilton|url=http://kotaku.com/heres-a-complete-schedule-of-e3-press-conferences-509568885 |title=Here's A Complete Schedule Of E3 Press Conferences |publisher=Kotaku|date=2013-06-06 |accessdate=18 June 2013}}</ref> However, [[Nintendo]] took a different approach by holding no traditional press conference. Instead, Nintendo held \"a few smaller events that are specifically focused on our software lineup\", and aired a special episode of  [[List of Nintendo Direct shows|Nintendo Direct]] to focus on upcoming U.S. releases and new game unveilings.<ref>{{cite web|author=Andrew Goldfarb|url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2013/04/25/no-nintendo-press-conference-at-e3-2013 |title=No Nintendo Press Conference at E3 2013 |publisher=IGN |date=2013-04-25 |accessdate=13 May 2013}}</ref>\n\n===Konami===\nKonami held its 3rd annual pre-E3 show on June 6. The presentation showcased the company's 40th anniversary and its ''[[Dance Dance Revolution#Use in schools|Dance Dance Revolution: Classroom Edition]]'' initiative, before providing updates on upcoming game releases. This included the games ''[[Castlevania: Lords of Shadow 2]]'', ''[[Pro Evolution Soccer 2014]]'' and ''[[Metal Gear Solid V: The Phantom Pain]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title=E3 2013: Konami\u2019s pre-E3 2013 roundup|url=http://www.technologytell.com/gaming/113220/e3-2013-konamis-pre-e3-2013-roundup/|publisher=TechnologyTell|accessdate=18 June 2013|author=Jonathan Gronli|date=2013-06-07}}</ref>\n\n===Microsoft===\nMicrosoft's press conference took place on June 10 at 9:30am. The company announced a November 2013 release date for its forthcoming [[Xbox One]] console, priced at $499.<ref>{{cite web|title=At E3, Microsoft Sets Out to Win Back Gamers|url=https://www.wired.com/gamelife/2013/06/xbox-e3-2013-analysis/|publisher=Wired|accessdate=18 June 2013|author=Chris Kohler|date=2013-06-10}}</ref> The software lineup was also revealed, including ''[[Dead Rising 3]]'', ''[[Quantum Break]]'', ''[[Ryse: Son of Rome]]'' and the next installment of ''[[Halo (series)|Halo]]'',<ref>{{cite web|title=E3 2013: Microsoft Comes Out Swinging|url=http://uk.ign.com/articles/2013/06/10/e3-2013-microsoft-comes-out-swinging|publisher=IGN|accessdate=18 June 2013|author=Keza MacDonald|date=2013-06-10}}</ref> later revealed to be [[Halo 5: Guardians]].\n\nControversy arose during Microsoft's showcase of ''[[Killer Instinct (2013 video game)|Killer Instinct]]'' when an apparent reference to [[rape]] was made between the on-stage demonstrators. Microsoft later apologized for the incident and stated that the remarks were not scripted.<ref>{{cite news|title=The Rape 'Joke' at Microsoft's E3 Reveal Is a Bigger Deal Than Another Bad 'Joke'|url=http://www.theatlanticwire.com/technology/2013/06/microsoft-e3-rape-joke/66092/|accessdate=18 June 2013|newspaper=The Atlantic Wire|date=2013-06-10|author=Rebecca Greenfield}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=E3 audience offended by \"rape joke\" at Microsoft Xbox One event|url=http://www.cbsnews.com/8301-205_162-57588725/e3-audience-offended-by-rape-joke-at-microsoft-xbox-one-event/|accessdate=18 June 2013|newspaper=CBS News|date=2013-06-11|author=Chenda Ngak}}</ref>\n\n===Electronic Arts===\nElectronic Arts' press conference took place on June 10 at 1:00pm. Among the new titles shown were the racing game ''[[Need for Speed: Rivals]]'', the parkour simulator ''[[Mirror's Edge Catalyst]]'' and the first-person shooters ''[[Battlefield 4]]'' and ''[[Titanfall]]''. [[EA Sports]] announced a number of new releases, such as ''[[Madden NFL 25]]'', ''[[NBA Live 14]]'', ''[[FIFA 14]]'', ''[[NHL 14]]'' and ''[[EA Sports UFC]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title=E3 2013 - EA Press Conference Recap|url=http://www.co-optimus.com/article/10324/e3-2013-ea-press-conference-recap.html|publisher=Co-Optimus|accessdate=18 June 2013|author=Mike Katsufrakis|date=2013-06-10}}</ref>\n\n===Ubisoft===\nUbisoft's press conference took place on June 10 at 3:00pm. Upcoming action-adventure games included ''[[Watch Dogs]]'' and the sequels ''[[Assassin's Creed IV: Black Flag]]'' and ''[[Tom Clancy's Splinter Cell: Blacklist]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title=Highlights from Ubisoft\u2019s E3 2013 Press Conference: The Crew, The Division, and More|url=https://arstechnica.com/gaming/2013/06/analysis-the-one-two-combo-sony-used-to-knock-microsoft-out-of-e3-2013/|publisher=Diital Trends|accessdate=18 June 2013|author=Kevin Kelly|date=2013-06-10}}</ref> Two new franchises \u2013 ''[[The Crew (video game)|The Crew]]'' and ''[[The Division (video game)|The Division]]'' \u2013 were also announced.\n\n===Sony===\nSony's press conference took place on June 10 at 6:00pm. The [[PlayStation 4]] was publicly shown for the first time, retailing at $399.<ref>{{cite web|author=Kyle Orland|title=Analysis: The one-two combo Sony used to knock Microsoft out of E3 2013|url=http://www.edge-online.com/features/e3-2013-sony-press-conference-review/|publisher=Ars Techinca|accessdate=18 June 2013|date=2013-06-11}}</ref> The software lineup included ''[[Infamous: Second Son]]'', ''[[The Order: 1886]]'' and ''[[Killzone: Shadow Fall]]''. There were also new games introduced for the [[PlayStation 3]], such as ''[[Gran Turismo 6]]'', ''[[Beyond: Two Souls]]'' and ''[[The Last of Us]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title=E3 2013: Sony's Knock-Out Blow|url=http://uk.ign.com/articles/2013/06/11/e3-2013-sonys-knock-out-blow|publisher=IGN|accessdate=18 June 2013|author=Keza MacDonald|date=2013-06-10}}</ref>\n\n===Nintendo===\nThe E3 edition of [[Nintendo Direct]] aired at June 11 at 7:00am. Nintendo first showed a new trailer for the [[Nintendo 3DS]] titles [[Pok\u00e9mon X and Y|''Pok\u00e9mon X'' and ''Y'']], including the announcement of a new Pok\u00e9mon type, Fairy Type. After that, Nintendo focused mostly on showing upcoming [[Wii U]] titles. Nintendo showed some of the third-party and digital titles coming to the Wii U, and more about previously announced games such as ''[[X (2014 video game)|X]]'', ''[[The Wonderful 101]]'', ''[[The Legend of Zelda: The Wind Waker HD]]'', and the first gameplay footage of ''[[Bayonetta 2]]''. Among the new games announced for Wii U were the new installments of Super Smash Bros., ''[[Super Smash Bros. for Nintendo 3DS]]'' and ''[[Super Smash Bros. for Wii U]]'', ''[[Super Mario 3D World]]'', ''[[Mario Kart 8]]'', and ''[[Donkey Kong Country: Tropical Freeze]]''.\n\n==List of notable exhibitors==\nThis is a list of major video game exhibitors who made appearances at E3 2013.<ref name=autogenerated1 />\n<!--Do NOT add any companies to the list without a reference from the official E3 site, a major gaming site or a direct confirmation from the developer/publisher that they would be exhibiting at E3-->\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n|valign=top|\n* [[505 Games]]\n* [[Activision Blizzard]]\n* [[Atlus]]\n* [[Bethesda Softworks|Bethesda]]\n* [[Capcom]]\n|valign=top|\n* [[CD Projekt Red]]\n* [[Koch Media|Deep Silver]]\n* [[Disney Interactive Studios|Disney]]\n* [[Electronic Arts]]\n* [[Konami]]\n|valign=top|\n* [[Microsoft Studios|Microsoft]]\n* [[Namco Bandai Games|Namco Bandai]]\n* [[Nintendo]]\n* [[Sega]]\n* [[Sony Computer Entertainment|Sony]]\n|valign=top|\n* [[Square Enix]]\n* [[Tecmo Koei]]\n* [[Ubisoft]]\n* [[Warner Bros. Interactive Entertainment|Warner Bros.]]\n* [[Marvelous USA|XSEED Games]]\n|}\n\n==List of featured games==\nThis is a list of notable titles that appeared at E3 2013.<ref>{{cite web|title=So, The Games of E3 2013. When Are They Coming Out Again?|url=http://kotaku.com/so-the-games-of-e3-2013-when-are-they-coming-out-agai-513399138|publisher=Kotaku|accessdate=18 June 2013|author=Andr\u00e1s Neltz|dat